.SH NAME
DBIx::Class::Migration::ShareDirBuilder \- Build a target_dir in /share
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&    use DBIx::Class::Migration::ShareDirBuilder;
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
This is a utility class that build the path to a distribution's \f(CW\*(C`/share\*(C'\fR
directory, whether the distribution is installed (via \f(CW\*(C`make install\*(C'\fR or if
it is in development.
.PP
This probably isn't really user servicable, although if you need to make a
custom \f(CW\*(C`target_dir\*(C'\fR builder, you could look at this for example.
